AVIAN INFLUENZA, HUMAN (35): CHINA (SHANGHAI, JIANGSU) H7N9 UPDATE
******************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

In this update:
[1] No epidemic link
[2] Jiangsu
[3] Shanghai, Jiangsu
[4] Taiwan: screening results
[5] WHO GAR report, 7 Apr 2013

******
[1] No epidemic link
Date: Mon 8 Apr 2012
Source: Xinhua News Agency [summ., edited]
http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/health/2013-04/08/c_132292088.htm


No epidemic link has been detected so far among the H7N9 infections in China, an official of the country's health authority said on Monday [8 Apr 2013]. The authorities have monitored 621 close contacts of the infected patients and to date there is no abnormality among them, said Liang Wannian, director of the H7N9 influenza prevention and control office under the National Health and Family Planning Commission (NHFPC).

As of midnight [7 Apr 2013], the NHFPC had received 21 reports of human infection of the H7N9 avian influenza virus, Liang said at a press conference held by the commission. According to Liang, 10 of the reported cases were found in Shanghai, 6 in Jiangsu Province, 2 in Anhui Province, and 3 in Zhejiang Province, Liang said, adding that 4 patients in Shanghai and 2 in Zhejiang died of the disease.

[Byline: Lu Hui)

