******
[2] Jiangsu
Date: Mon 8 Apr 2013
Source: China News [in Chinese, trans. Mod.YMA, edited]
http://www.chinanews.com/gn/2013/04-08/4711890.shtml


On 8 Apr 2013, the Health Department in Jiangsu reports that 2 more human cases of H7N9 avian influenza virus infection were confirmed in Jiangsu province, increasing the total number of confirmed cases to 8.

The 1st case is a 85-year-old retired man from Xiaguan district, Nanjing city. He became sick on 28 Mar 2013 and was admitted to a hospital in Nanjing city on 1 Apr 2013. The expert group in Jiangsu province confirmed the infection with H7N9 avian influenza virus in the afternoon of 8 Apr 2013. He is now in critical condition. The investigation revealed 34 close contacts who are all well.

The 2nd case is a 25-year-old unemployed woman from Runzhou district in Zhenjiang city. On 30 Mar 2013, she became sick and was admitted to a hospital in Zhenjiang city. She was confirmed to have H7N9 avian influenza virus infection in the afternoon of 8 Apr 2013 by the expert group in Jiangsu province. She is also in critical condition and so far 18 close contacts do not have abnormal symptoms.

In addition, the expert group in Jiangsu province excluded one suspected case from Wujiang district in Suzhou city in the afternoon of 8 Apr 2013.

The Health Department in Jiangsu province is implementing rescue efforts and epidemic prevention and control measures.

[Byline: Zhu Xiaoying]

