******
[4] Taiwan: screening results
Date: Mon 8 Apr 2013
Source: Xinhua News Agency [edited]
http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/china/2013-04/08/c_132293134.htm


Taiwan's disease control authority said Monday [8 Apr 2013] that 4 of 7 suspected human infections of H7N9 bird flu that were reported over the last 24 hours have been ruled out, although the remaining 3 cases are still being tested.

Since 3 Apr 2013, 27 suspected cases have been reported on the island, with 24 of the patients testing negative for the virus, Chang Feng-yee, chief of the island's disease control authority, said at a press conference. However, Chang did not provide details about the 3 people who are still undergoing tests.

The island has enhanced surveillance and intensified the sanitization of poultry farms as preventative efforts against the H7N9 bird flu, as the mainland has reported an increasing number of cases.

